<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-2095] Consider replacing concatenation into slf4j loggers with interpolation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-2095</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In most cases these statements are protected by a conditional to check if the logger is enabled so there shouldn&apos;t be a real performance impact, replacing concatenation would result in code aligned with modern logging recommendations, and improve perf in a few cases that aren&apos;t guarded (though at a glance I don&apos;t see any in hot paths).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
