                            <comment id="17149637" author="michael-o" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2020 18:43:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you provide a specific example you see improveworthy?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17149640" author="ckozak" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2020 18:48:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Of course &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/httpcomponents-client/pull/232&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/httpcomponents-client/pull/232&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This allows us to remove some of the conditionals for constant invocations (those with overloads that don&apos;t include var-args, that&apos;s slf4j methods with two or fewer parameters which are direct references)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17149641" author="ckozak" created="Wed, 1 Jul 2020 18:50:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To provide a bit more context, using log4j2 we can format a message and write it to disk without any allocation, however using concatenation we&apos;ve already done a great deal of allocation before calling the logger.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
